                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d600">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">822.01/9–747: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Ecuador</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-09-08T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 8, 1947—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>266. <gloss target="#t_urtel1">Urtel</gloss> 388, Sept 7.<note n="14"
                        xml:id="d600fn1">Not printed.</note> Dept does not wish to take any action
                    in respect of Ecuadoran recognition at this time. Situation is not yet
                    considered clear and it is considered preferable to await developments
                    particularly from Sept 15 meeting of Congress and in general to have clear
                    picture of whether regime manifests all qualities of stable <hi rend="italic">de
                        facto</hi> govt. Also we will probably wish to await views of a rather
                    substantial body of other American republics.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
